<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Tigran Gambaryan, Binance=E2=80=99s head of fi=
nancial-crime compliance, flew to Nigeria=E2=80=99s capital to solve a prob=
lem: The government had blamed the world=E2=80=99s largest crypto exchange =
for crashing the currency. ...</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Nigerian authorities detained Gambaryan and a =
colleague, Nadeem Anjarwalla, a U.K. and Kenyan national and Binance=E2=80=
=99s regional manager for Africa, according to the men=E2=80=99s families.<=
/p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The Binance employees, who are being held in a=
 guarded house, haven=E2=80=99t been charged with any crimes. The governmen=
t, which invited them to Nigeria for meetings, hasn=E2=80=99t publicly disc=
ussed the detentions. =E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Because the government rationed who could exch=
ange the local currency for the dollar and at what exchange rate, many soug=
ht refuge in digital currencies pegged to the U.S. dollar, known as stablec=
oins.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The stablecoin trade in essence became a black=
 market, displaying an unofficial exchange rate between the local currency,=
 the naira, and the dollar that was much weaker than the government=E2=80=
=99s rates. Binance, the most popular exchange, became the go-to place to c=
heck that black-market rate, according to currency traders.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Bayo Onanuga, a special adviser to the Nigeria=
n president, accused Binance of setting the exchange rate for Nigeria and h=
ijacking the role of the central bank.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CCrypto should be banned in our countr=
y or else this bleeding of our currency will continue unabated,=E2=80=9D he=
 wrote in a post on X.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusi=
ness.com/click/34684872.258367/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuZnQuY29tL2NvbnRlbnQvOWMxMzk0=
